component SkillInstaller {
  goal {
    Install valid agent skills bundled with the selected Sigil CLI distribution into global or project locations for supported coding agents without replacing unrelated content.

    Keep skill assets version-aligned with the executable selected for installation while allowing future skills without command-code changes.
  }

  interface {
    SkillInstallation {
      installSkills(scope?, agents?, sourceDirectory?, targetRoot?, userHome?) returns the selected scope, agent targets, and one installed, updated, existing, copied, or conflicted result per destination

      scope defaults to global and accepts global or project

      agents default to codex, claude, opencode, and pi

      sourceDirectory defaults to the integrations/skills directory resolved from the running Sigil installation

      Codex, OpenCode, and Pi share .agents/skills for the selected scope

      Claude Code uses .claude/skills for the selected scope

      global scope resolves targets from userHome

      project scope resolves targets from targetRoot or the current working directory
    }

    InstalledSkillDiscovery {
      resolveInstalledSkillsDirectory(moduleUrl?, executablePath?) returns the first available installation-relative skills directory

      returned source, target, and link paths are resolved absolute host paths
    }
  }
}

expand SkillInstaller {
  state {
    installable skills are the sorted immediate non-hidden directories containing SKILL.md in the selected integrations/skills directory

    each destination is absent, managed by Sigil, or an unmanaged conflict
  }

  logic {
    Resolve skills beside the selected executable before considering source-module development fallbacks.

    Executable lookup checks executableDirectory/../integrations/skills before executableDirectory/integrations/skills.

    File-module fallback checks moduleDirectory/../integrations/skills before moduleDirectory/../../../integrations/skills.

    Deduplicate candidate paths, select the first existing directory, and report every checked path when none exists.

    A versioned layout resolves version/bin/sigil to version/integrations/skills.

    Source development may resolve the repository-level integrations/skills directory relative to installer.ts.

    Install only immediate non-hidden source directories containing SKILL.md.

    Reject an installation source that is missing or contains no installable skill directories.

    Deduplicate destinations shared by Codex, OpenCode, and Pi before filesystem changes.

    Preflight every destination before changing any managed installation.

    Prefer relative directory links when the host supports them.

    Fall back to a managed directory copy when a permitted link cannot be created.

    Record enough managed installation metadata to distinguish Sigil-owned destinations from unrelated content.

    Retarget or replace an older Sigil-managed installation when the selected executable owns a newer or different skill version.

    Refuse to replace any destination that is not recorded as Sigil-managed.

    Create or update project-local skill .gitignore files with one root-anchored entry for every managed skill name.

    A newly created managed .gitignore starts with # Managed by sigil skill install.

    Preserve unrelated ignore rules, existing newline style, and existing managed entries without duplication.

    Retain existing ignore entries when a previously installed skill is no longer present in the selected source.

    Return destination records in stable skill and agent order with their source, target, and installation status.
  }

  constraints {
    Skill names are discovered from integrations/skills and are never hardcoded into command logic.

    Hidden entries, files, source symlinks, and directories without SKILL.md are not installable skills.

    Links use host-native relative targets and remain valid while the repository and installation retain the same relative layout.

    Directory symlink type is explicit for Windows when link creation is permitted.

    Path equality is case-insensitive on Windows and case-sensitive on macOS and Linux.

    An existing unmanaged file, directory, or symlink is a conflict and is never replaced.

    Conflict preflight completes for every destination before any managed installation is changed.

    Project git ignore entries cover generated skill links or copies while the ignore file itself remains repository content.

    The invoked executable owns source-version selection; skill install does not inspect workspace configuration to choose or switch binaries.

    Filesystem and host permission failures propagate as CLI runtime failures.
  }

  cases {
    Global installation exposes one shared skill to Codex, OpenCode, and Pi and one Claude-compatible installation.

    Project installation creates the equivalent destinations inside only the current repository.

    A Windows host without directory-link permission receives a managed copy.

    Reinstalling from a newer selected CLI updates older managed skill destinations.

    An unmanaged destination named sigil aborts installation without changing other destinations.

    A distribution containing multiple valid skills installs them without a CLI code change.

    Repeating installation against current managed destinations reports every skill as existing and leaves project .gitignore files unchanged.

    An existing .gitignore keeps unrelated rules and receives only missing managed skill entries.

    A selected version/bin/sigil resolves assets from the same version/integrations/skills directory before source fallbacks.

    Two repositories invoking different versioned binaries link to the skill assets owned by their respective binaries.

    An empty integrations/skills directory reports a runtime failure and creates no target content.
  }
}
